author: @sj1795
text: I'm not going to lie. I've LOVED all your videos up until the Pandas series. I've really been struggling; not because of you, because of me. Alex you're a gem. The ONLY reason I'm making it through Pandas is because of your instructions, which are always so clear and easy to follow.   As I've worked my way through your bootcamp series I've discovered that the process of coding is like learning all new things. You have ebbs and flows where it's a real struggle as you learn the new material, then you reach one mountain top and get super excited because the material finally "clicks", and then you're back at the bottom climbing another mountain. lol I know pandas and numpy are extremely important concepts to grasp in Python. I'm just struggling along waiting for them to "click". However, you make it soooo worth the struggle. I've learned SO MUCH already. I appreciate YOU. As always, THANK YOU!!
